||6||0||colspan=2|\u2014||48||1\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Manchester City F.C. season|2014\u201315]]\n|Premier League\n|29||1||1||0||6||1||0||0||36||2\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Manchester City F.C. season|2015\u201316]]\n|Premier League\n|13||0||6||0||3||0||colspan=2|\u2014||22||0\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Manchester City F.C. season|2016\u201317]]\n|Premier League\n|20||1||5||1||7||0||colspan=2|\u2014||32||2\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n! 230 !! 9 !! 48 !! 2 !! 54 !! 1 !! 1 !! 0 !! 333 !! 12\n|-\n| rowspan=4|[[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]\n|[[2017\u201318 West Ham United F.C. season|2017\u201318]]\n|Premier League\n|37||0||2||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||39||0\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 West Ham United F.C. season|2018\u201319]]\n|Premier League\n|26||0||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||27||0\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 West Ham United F.C. season|2019\u201320]]\n|Premier League\n|10||0||4||1||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||14||1\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!73!!0!!7!!1!!0!!0!!0!!0!!80!!1\n|-\n! colspan=3|Career total\n!448!!20!!60!!3!!83!!1!!3!!0!!594!!24\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|match played 10 November 2016}}<ref>{{NFT player |id=12065 |name=Zabaleta, Pablo |accessdate=11 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|+ Appearances and goals by national team and year\n|-\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=10|[[Argentina national football team|Argentina]]\n|2005||2||0\n|-\n|2006||2||0\n|-\n|2008||3||0\n|-\n|2010||1||0\n|-\n|2011||13||0\n|-\n|2012||7||0\n|-\n|2013||7||0\n|-\n|2014||12||0\n|-\n|2015||7||0\n|-\n|2016||4||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total||58||0\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n[[File:2011 FA Cup Final Victory Parade (3).jpg|thumb|right|Zabaleta with the FA Cup on Manchester City's [[2011 FA Cup Final|2011]] victory parade in May 2011]]\n\n'''Manchester City'''\n*[[Premier League]]: [[2011\u201312 Premier League|2011\u201312]], [[2013\u201314 Premier League|2013\u201314]]<ref name=\"Premier Pleague Profile\">{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/players/3654/Pablo-Zabaleta/overview |title=Pablo Zabaleta: Overview |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=18 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[FA Cup]]: [[2010\u201311 FA Cup|2010\u201311]];<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/13346941 |title=Man City 1\u20130 Stoke |first=Phil |last=McNulty |publisher=BBC Sport |date=14 May 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140525071238/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/13346941 |archivedate=25 May 2014}}</ref> runner-up: [[2012\u201313 FA Cup|2012\u201313]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/22409634 |title=Man City 0\u20131 Wigan |first=Phil |last=McNulty |publisher=BBC Sport |date=11 May 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160112212927/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/22409634 |archivedate=12 January 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Football League Cup]]: [[2013\u201314 Football League Cup|2013\u201314]],<ref name=2014LeagueCupFinal/> [[2015\u201316 Football League Cup|2015\u201316]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/35624164 |title=Liverpool 1\u20131 Manchester City |first=Phil |last=McNulty |publisher=BBC Sport |date=28 February 2016 |accessdate=27 April 2019}}</ref>\n*[[FA Community Shield]]: [[2012 FA Community Shield|2012]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19133978 |title=Chelsea 2\u20133 Man City |first=Ben |last=Smith |publisher=BBC Sport |date=12 August 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121002518/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19133978 |archivedate=21 January 2016}}</ref>\n \t\n'''Individual'''\n*[[PFA Team of the Year]]: [[PFA Team of the Year (2010s)#Premier League 4|2012\u201313 Premier League]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/22331030 |title=Gareth Bale wins PFA Player of Year and Young Player awards |publisher=BBC Sport |date=28 April 2013 |accessdate=18 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] Player of the Month: [[2008\u201309 Manchester City F.C. season#Thomas Cook Player of the Month awards|January 2009]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Awards time for Craig and Pablo |url=http://www.mcfc.co.uk/News/Club-news/2009/March/Awards-time-for-Craig-and-Pablo |date=9 March 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120729062924/http://www.mcfc.co.uk/News/Club-news/2009/March/Awards-time-for-Craig-and-Pablo |archivedate=29 July 2012 |website=Manchester City FC |accessdate=29 June 2016}}</ref> [[2012\u201313 Manchester City F.C. season#Etihad Player of the Month awards|December 2012]],<ref>{{Cite web|title=Etihad Player of the Month: Pablo Zabaleta|url=http://www.mcfc.co.uk/citytv/Features/2013/January/Etihad-Player-of-the-Month-Pablo-Zabaleta|publisher=Manchester City F.C.|accessdate=16 July 2015}}</ref> January 2013<ref>{{Cite web|title= Etihad Player of the Month: Pablo Zabaleta|url=http://www.mcfc.co.uk/citytv/Features/2013/February/Etihad-Player-of-the-Month-Pablo-Zabaleta|publisher=Manchester City F.C.|accessdate=16 July 2015}}</ref>\n*[[FIFPro World XI]] 5th team: 2013,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/news-and-comment/fifpro-announces-reserve-teams-of-the-year-but-luis-suarez-and-arjen-robben-wont-be-laughing-while-9062047.html#gallery |title=FifPro announces reserve Teams of the Year \u2013 but Luis Suarez and Arjen Robben won't be laughing while Iker Casillas is somehow named the second best goalkeeper of 2013|newspaper=The Independent|date=15 January 2014|accessdate=1 October 2017}}</ref> 2014<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifpro.org/news/fifa-fifpro-world-xi-the-reserve-teams/en/ |title=FIFA FIFPro World XI: the reserve teams \u2013 FIFPro World Players' Union |publisher=FIFPro |date=15 January 2015 |accessdate=1 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414193942/https://fifpro.org/news/fifa-fifpro-world-xi-the-reserve-teams/en/ |archive-date=14 April 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20150315020126/http://www.mcfc.co.uk/Teams/First-team/Defenders/Pablo-Zabaleta Manchester City profile]\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards\n| bg = gold\n| fg = navy\n| list1 = \n{{2012\u201313 Premier League PFA Team of the Year}}\n{{Manchester City F.C. Player of the Year}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Argentina squads\n| bg = #6AB5FF\n| fg = white\n| bordercolor = #00355E\n| list1 = \n{{Argentina men's football squad 2008 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Argentina squad 2011 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Argentina squad 2014 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Argentina squad 2015 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n}}\n{{West Ham United F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zabaleta, Pablo}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Buenos Aires]]\n[[Category:Argentine footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football fullbacks]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:San Lorenzo footballers]]\n[[Category:RCD Espanyol footballers]]\n[[Category:Manchester City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:West Ham United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic footballers of Argentina]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for Argentina]]\n[[Category:2011 Copa Am\u00e9rica players]]\n[[Category:2014 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:2015 Copa Am\u00e9rica players]]\n[[Category:Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Naturalised citizens of Spain]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate sportspeople in Spain]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in football]]\n[[Category:Argentine people of Basque descent]]\n[[Category:Argentina under-20 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentina international footballers]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:Association football commentators]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Argentine footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}}\n{{Spanish name|Zabaleta|Girod}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Pablo Zabaleta\n| image          = Hertha BSC vs. West Ham United 20190731 (127).jpg\n| image_size     = 200\n| caption        = Zabaleta with [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in 2019\n| fullname       = Pablo Javier Zabaleta Girod<ref>{{cite web|title=List of Players under Written Contract Registered Between 01/08/2013 and 31/08/2013|url=http://www.thefa.com/~/media/files/thefaportal/governance-docs/registrations/august-2013.ashx|publisher=The Football Association|format=PDF|accessdate=2 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140811083049/http://www.thefa.com/~/media/files/thefaportal/governance-docs/registrations/august-2013.ashx|archive-date=11 August 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1985|1|16|df=y}}<ref name=\"FIFA 2014\">{{cite web |title=2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil List of Players |url=https://www.fifadata.com/document/fwc/2014/pdf/fwc_2014_squadlists.pdf |website=FIFA |accessdate=30 January 2020 |pages=2 |format=PDF}}</ref>\n| birth_place    = [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina\n| height         = 1.74 m<ref>{{cite web |title=Pablo Zabaleta |url=https://www.whufc.com/teams/first-team/squad/pablo-zabaleta |publisher=West Ham United F.C. |access-date=12 October 2017}}</ref>\n| position       = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]]\n| currentclub    = [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]\n| clubnumber     = 5\n| youthyears1    = 1995\u20131997\n| youthclubs1    = Obras Sanitarias\n| youthyears2    = 1997\u20132002\n| youthclubs2    = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]]\n| years1         = 2002\u20132005\n| clubs1         = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]]\n| caps1          = 66\n| goals1         = 8\n| years2         = 2005\u20132008\n| clubs2         = [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]]\n| caps2          = 79\n| goals2         = 3\n| years3         = 2008\u20132017\n| clubs3         = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]\n| caps3          = 230\n| goals3         = 9\n| years4         = 2017\u2013\n| clubs4         = [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]\n| caps4          = 72\n| goals4         = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2003\u20132005\n| nationalteam1  = [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina U20]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 28\n| nationalgoals1 = 4\n| nationalyears2 = 2008\n| nationalteam2  = [[Argentina national under-23 football team|Argentina U23]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 9\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2005\u2013\n| nationalteam3  = [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]]\n| nationalcaps3  = 58\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry|{{ARG}}}}\n{{MedalSport |Men's [[Football at the Summer Olympics|Football]]}}\n{{MedalGold  |[[2008 Summer Olympics|2008]] |[[Football at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|Team Competition]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIFA World Cup]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]]|[[Argentina national football team|Team]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[2015 Copa Am\u00e9rica|2015]]|[[Argentina national football team|Team]]}}\n| club-update    = 22 January 2020\n| nationalteam-update = 11 November 2016\n}}\n'''Pablo Javier Zabaleta Girod'''  ({{IPA-es|\u02c8pa\u03b2lo sa\u03b2a\u02c8leta|am}}; born 16 January 1985) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]] for English {{English football updater|WestHamU}} club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]]. Zabaleta can operate on both sides of the pitch as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|full-back]] and is known for his tenacious style of play, and has [[Captain (association football)|captained]] his club on numerous occasions.\n\nWith [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], Zabaleta won all of English football's major honours: the [[FA Cup]] ([[2010\u201311 FA Cup|2011]]), the Premier League ([[2011\u201312 Premier League|2012]] and [[2013\u201314 Premier League|2014]]), the [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] ([[2013\u201314 Football League Cup|2014]] and [[2015\u201316 Football League Cup|2016]]) and the [[FA Community Shield|Community Shield]] ([[2012 FA Community Shield|2012]]). Before joining Manchester City, Zabaleta played for [[La Liga]] club [[RCD Espanyol]], where he won the [[2005\u201306 Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/football/players/pablo-zabaleta/|title=Pablo Zabaleta|accessdate=22 April 2014|publisher=Eurosport}}</ref> He made 333 appearances over nine seasons for Manchester City before signing for London-based club West Ham United in the summer of 2017.\n\nA full international since 2005, Zabaleta represented Argentina at the [[2011 Copa Am\u00e9rica|2011]] and [[2015 Copa Am\u00e9rica]], and was part of their team which finished as runners-up in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]]. He was also in their team which won gold at the [[Football at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2008 Olympics]].\n\n==Club career==\n===San Lorenzo===\nBorn in [[Buenos Aires]], Zabaleta was raised in [[Arrecifes]]. He began his career at [[Club Atl\u00e9tico San Lorenzo de Almagro]] in 2002 after progressing through their youth ranks, having been signed at the age of 12 from local club ''Obras Sanitarias''. He started playing as a [[defensive midfielder]] but eventually moved to the right side of midfield.\n\n===Espanyol===\nZabaleta was transferred to [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] in 2005 for \u20ac3 million after being [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina under-20]]s [[Captain (association football)|captain]] in the [[2005 FIFA World Youth Championship]], which Argentina won. During the [[2005\u201306 La Liga|2005\u201306 season]], Zabaleta helped Espanyol to win the [[2005\u201306 Copa del Rey|Copa del Rey]], playing the full 90 minutes in the 4\u20131 defeat of [[Real Zaragoza]] in [[2006 Copa del Rey Final|the final]].<ref name=\"paradise\">{{Cite news |title=Zabaleta rejects Juventus in favour of move to 'paradise' |last=Taylor |first=Daniel |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2008/aug/29/manchestercity.espanyolzabaleta |newspaper=The Guardian |date=29 August 2008 |location=London}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2007, Zabaleta suffered a [[shoulder]] injury that kept him off the pitch for almost three months, already having established himself as an undisputed first team choice. Later in the season, he featured in the [[2006\u201307 UEFA Cup]] [[2007 UEFA Cup Final|final]], where Espanyol lost on penalties to fellow Spanish side [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]].\n\n===Manchester City===\n====2008\u20132012====\n[[File:Pablo Zabaleta ready to throw vs Bolton.jpg|thumb|upright|Zabaleta playing for [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in 2009]]\n\nIn the summer of 2008, Zabaleta transferred to [[Premier League]] club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] after rejecting an offer from [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]. He stated upon joining that \"The offer is impossible to reject and not just because of the money ... Juventus also wanted me but I wanted to come to England, and to Manchester.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2008/aug/29/manchestercity.espanyolzabaleta|title=Premier League: Manchester City target Pablo Zabaleta says he turned down Juventus for City|first=Daniel|last=Taylor|date=29 August 2008|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref> Having passed a medical and agreed personal terms, Zabaleta completed a five-year deal with City on 31 August 2008 for an undisclosed fee, believed to be the buy-out clause Zabaleta had attached to his contract of around \u00a36.45 million.<ref name=paradise/> Zabaleta joined a day before Manchester City was bought by the [[Abu Dhabi United Group]], led by [[Sheikh Mansour]], which enabled a wealth of investment in the club.\n\nOn 13 September 2008, Zabaleta made his debut for Manchester City in a 3\u20131 defeat to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] at the [[City of Manchester Stadium]]. On 5 October, he received his first [[Penalty card#Red card|red card]] in English football when he was sent off in a 3\u20132 loss to [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in his fourth Premier League appearance. He scored his first goal for City on 17 January 2009, the only goal of the game in a 1\u20130 league win over [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/7815631.stm|title=Man City 1\u20130 Wigan|publisher=BBC|date=17 January 2009|accessdate=2 January 2010|first=Chris|last=Bevan}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 November 2010, Zabaleta scored his second Premier League goal in Manchester City's 4\u20131 win against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]. In the same match, he [[Assist (football)|assisted]] a [[Carlos Tevez]] goal, helping his compatriot to earn his ninth goal for the club during the [[2010\u201311 Manchester City F.C. season|2010\u201311]] season.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Fulham 1\u20134 Manchester City |url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report/_/id/293144?cc=5901 |publisher=ESPN Soccernet |date=21 November 2010}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 January 2011, Zabaleta played his 100th game for Manchester City in all competitions, coming off the bench against [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] in a 1\u20130 win at Eastlands. Two weeks later, on 15 January, Zabaleta made his second assist of the season in a 4\u20133 win over [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Manchester 4\u20133 Wolves |url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/match?id=293123&cc=5901 |publisher=ESPN Soccernet |date=15 January 2011}}</ref> This win meant that City went top of [[2010\u201311 Premier League|the league]] above [[Manchester derby|local rivals]] [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]. However, City's title challenge faded with a loss of form in February and March 2011.\n\nOn 1 May 2011, Zabaleta scored his second goal of the season in a Premier League match against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]. This secured a 2\u20131 win for the Citizens and put them seven points ahead of [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] in the race for [[2011\u201312 UEFA Champions League|fourth place]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Manchester City 2\u20131 West Ham |url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report/_/id/293139?cc=5739 |publisher=ESPN Soccernet |date=1 May 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 May 2011, Zabaleta appeared as an 88th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for Carlos Tevez in the [[2011 FA Cup Final]] as Manchester City beat [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] 1\u20130.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gibbs|first=Thom|title=FA Cup final 2011: Manchester City v Stoke City live|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/competitions/fa-cup/8513729/FA-Cup-final-2011-Manchester-City-v-Stoke-City-live.html|accessdate=6 March 2014|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=14 May 2011|location=London}}</ref>\n\nIn the summer of 2011, it was reported that Italian club [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] were keen on signing Zabaleta, but Manchester City insisted the player was not for sale<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenational.ae/sport/roma-want-zabaleta-from-manchester-city-1.576072|title=Roma want Zabaleta from Manchester City|website=The National}}</ref> and Zabaleta agreed a three-year contract in July 2011. On 1 October 2011, Zabaleta started and played the full 90 minutes at right-back in a 4\u20130 win over [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]] at [[Ewood Park]] in the Premier League, as regular starter [[Micah Richards]] was not available. On 23 October, he was an unused substitute in the convincing 1\u20136 win over rivals Manchester United at [[Old Trafford]], with Richards starting at right-back.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Zabaleta agrees three-year deal |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/zabaleta-agrees-threeyear-deal-2318961.html |newspaper=The Independent |date=23 July 2011 |location=London}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2011, Zabaleta extended his contract with City until the summer of 2015. Zabaleta said, \"I'm in a very good team, and I try to do my best for the club, the team and the fans. I didn't think twice, I gave a quick answer because I was so happy to sign.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/15791957|title=Adam Johnson and Pablo Zabaleta extend their stay at Manchester City|date=18 November 2011|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=City tie down Johnson and Zabaleta |url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=1717452.html |date=18 November 2011 |publisher=[[UEFA]] |access-date=29 June 2016}}</ref> In his first three-and-a-half years at the club, Zabaleta emerged as a cult hero amongst the Manchester City fans who admire his never-say-die attitude and commitment to the club.\n\nOn 30 April 2012, he started and played the full 90 minutes in the right-back slot in a 1\u20130 victory over rivals Manchester United thanks to a first-half stoppage time header by [[Vincent Kompany]] from a corner at the City of Manchester Stadium. Zabaleta scored the first goal in City's dramatic 3\u20132 win over [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] on the final day of the [[2011\u201312 Premier League|season]], a result which secured the first league title for the club since 1968.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/17973148|title=Manchester City 3-2 QPR|date=13 May 2012|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref> On 9 December 2012, Zabaleta scored a late equalising goal in a 3\u20132 defeat to Manchester United.\n\n====2013\u20132017====\n[[File:Zabaleta Negredo league cup.JPG|thumb|upright|Zabaleta and [[\u00c1lvaro Negredo]] with the trophy after the [[2014 Football League Cup Final|2014 League Cup Final]]]]\n\nOn 1 January 2013, he scored the opening goal in a 3\u20130 win at the City of Manchester Stadium over Stoke City, doubling his goal tally from the previous season. On 25 January 2013, Zabaleta scored his third goal of the season and the only goal of the match in a 1\u20130 win away against Stoke City in the [[2012\u201313 FA Cup|FA Cup]], fourth round. His goal took Manchester City through to the fifth round.\n\nZabaleta was voted Manchester City's Player of the Month for both December 2012<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mcfc.co.uk/News/Team-news/2013/January/Zaba-wins-Etihad-prize|title=Zabaleta is Etihad Player of the Month|date=7 January 2013|publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref> and January 2013,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mcfc.co.uk/News/Team-news/2013/February/Zabaleta-wins-January-Etihad-Player-of-the-Month|title=Zabaleta voted Etihad Player of the Month|date=11 February 2013|publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref> and was stand-in captain for the club during [[Vincent Kompany]]'s injury absence between January and March 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/manchester-city-missing-uniteds-winning-1786570|title=Mind games: Manchester City are missing United's winning mentality, admits Pablo Zabaleta|date=26 March 2013|access-date=22 February 2015|newspaper=Daily Mirror}}</ref> He was the only City player to be named in the 2012\u201313 Premier League [[PFA Team of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Gareth Bale wins PFA Player of Year and Young Player awards|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/22331030|publisher=BBC Sport|date=28 April 2013|accessdate=2 May 2013}}</ref> After a superb season, Zabaleta was voted 2012\u201313 Manchester City Player of the Year.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mcfc.co.uk/news/team-news/2013/june/zabaleta-named-player-of-the-year|title=Pablo Zabaleta is Manchester City Player of the Year|date=4 June 2013|publisher=Manchester City F.C.|accessdate=21 June 2013}}</ref>\n\nZabaleta was sent off in the [[2013 FA Cup Final]] against Wigan Athletic for a second [[Penalty card#Yellow card|yellow card]] after a clear foul on [[Callum McManaman]] 84 minutes into the match. Wigan went on to win 1\u20130 through a [[Ben Watson (footballer, born July 1985)|Ben Watson]] goal in stoppage time. He was the third player to be sent off in an FA Cup final and first for the losing side.\n\nOn 2 March 2014, Zabaleta played the full 90 minutes as Manchester City beat [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] 3\u20131 in the [[2014 Football League Cup Final|2014 League Cup Final]] to complete a full set of major honours in English football.<ref name=2014LeagueCupFinal>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/26311649 |title=Manchester City 3\u20131 Sunderland |first=Phil |last=McNulty |publisher=BBC Sport |date=2 March 2014 |accessdate=27 April 2019}}</ref> On 21 April, he scored his first goal of the season in a 3\u20131 defeat of West Bromwich Albion at the City of Manchester Stadium.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/27017161|title=Man City 3\u20131 West Brom|date=21 April 2014|accessdate=22 April 2014|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 11 May, Zabaleta was part of the victory against West Ham that won Manchester City the Premier League, his second in three seasons.\n\nOn 21 September 2014, Zabaleta was sent off for a second [[Penalty card#Yellow card|yellow card]] due to a challenge on Chelsea's [[Diego Costa]]. Both players received a yellow card, Zabaleta for the initial challenge and Costa for his reaction.\n\nOn 21 August 2015, it was announced that Zabaleta was out for a month with knee injury.<ref>{{cite web|title=Manchester City's Pablo Zabaleta out for month with knee injury|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/34018567|publisher=BBC Sport|date=21 August 2015|accessdate=21 August 2015}}</ref> On 17 January 2016, Zabaleta reached 200 appearances for Manchester City in the club's 4\u20130 victory over [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Zabaleta proud to be 'half Mancunian' after 200th City appearance |url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/85/england/2016/01/17/19416502/zabaleta-proud-to-be-half-mancunian-after-300th-city |date=17 January 2016 |website=Goal.com |accessdate=29 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nZabaleta made 32 appearances in all competitions in the 2016\u201317 season scoring two goals; against [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] in the Premier League and against [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] in the FA Cup. His final appearance for Manchester City came on 16 May 2017, a 3\u20131 home win against [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39853090|title=Manchester City 3\u20131 West Bromwich Albion|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Chris|last=Bevan|date=16 May 2017|accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref> After the game he was praised by the City manager, [[Pep Guardiola]], as a \"legend\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/video/2017/may/17/manchester-city-guardiola-praises-legend-zabaleta-after-west-brom-win-video|title=Manchester City\u2019s Guardiola praises \u2018legend\u2019 Zabaleta after West Brom win \u2013 video|newspaper=The Guardian|date=17 May 2017}}</ref> Zabaleta was given a lifetime season ticket for Manchester City and a shirt that read \u201cZabaleta 333\u201d, to mark the number of City appearances he made.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/may/16/manchester-city-west-bromwich-albion-premier-league-match-report|title=Manchester City bid farewell to Pablo Zabaleta after crucial West Brom win|first=Jamie|last=Jackson|date=16 May 2017|newspaper=The Guardian}}</ref>\n\n===West Ham United===\nOn 26 May 2017, Zabaleta signed for [[Premier League]] club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] on a free transfer, agreeing to a two-year contract. He was given number five as his squad number.<ref>{{cite web|title=Joint-Chairman hails \u2018supreme professional\u2019 Zabaleta|url=http://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2017/may/26-may/joint-chairman-hails-supreme-professional-zabaleta|publisher=West Ham United F.C.|date=26 May 2017|accessdate=26 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 May 2018, [[Manuel Pellegrini]] was confirmed as manager of [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]],<ref name=WestHamIn>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44163423 |title=West Ham: Manuel Pellegrini named new manager at London Stadium |publisher=BBC Sport |date=22 May 2018 |accessdate=22 May 2018}}</ref> reuniting him with his former manager at [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].\n\nIn May 2019, Zabaleta extended his contract with West Ham Until the summer of 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2019/may/01-may/zabaleta-extends-hammers-contract-2020|title=Zabaleta extends Hammers contract to 2020 &#124; West Ham United|website=www.whufc.com}}</ref> On 5 January 2020, Zabaleta scored his first goal for West Ham, in a 2-0 win against [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]] in the FA Cup third round.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/uk-sports/2020/01/05/zabaleta-breaks-the-deadlock-as-west-ham-grind-past-gillingham/|title=Zabaleta breaks the deadlock as West Ham grind past Gillingham|website=www.expressandstar.com}}</ref> On 10 January 2020, in a match against [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]], Zabaleta became the first Argentinean, and only the third South American, to record 300 Premier League appearances. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.alairelibre.cl/noticias/deportes/futbol/liga-inglesa/pablo-zabaleta-se-transformo-en-el-tercer-sudamericano-en-jugar-300/2020-01-10/213801.html|title=Pablo Zabaleta se transform\u00f3 en el tercer sudamericano en jugar 300 partidos en la Premier League|website=www.alairelibre.cl}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n[[File:MessiZabaletaBanega.jpg|thumb|upright|Zabaleta (middle) lining up for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in 2014]]\n\nAt the age of 14, Zabaleta was called up by [[Hugo Tocalli]] to the Argentina under-15 squad. He took part in many youth tournaments, including the [[FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in [[2003 FIFA World Youth Championship|2003]] and [[2005 FIFA World Youth Championship|2005]], winning the latter in the [[Netherlands]]. He received over 75 caps to national youth sides, and started representing [[Argentina national football team|the senior side]] in 2005. He was also a member of the gold medal-winning team at the [[Football at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2008 Summer Olympics]], starting at right-back and playing all six matches.\n\nAfter the [[2010 FIFA World Cup]], for which Zabaleta was not selected by head coach [[Diego Maradona]], under the new Argentina manager he has established himself as first-choice right-back. On 1 June 2011, Zabaleta captained Argentina for the first time in a friendly against [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]].\n\nIn June 2014, Zabaleta was named in Argentina's squad for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/news/y=2014/m=6/news=demichelis-in-argentina-squad-as-trio-miss-out-2353431.html|title=Demichelis in Argentina squad as trio miss out|date=2 June 2014|accessdate=21 June 2014|publisher=FIFA}}</ref> He made his [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] debut in Argentina's 2\u20131 win over [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at the [[Est\u00e1dio do Maracan\u00e3]], playing the full match in defence.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/25285099|title=Argentina 2\u20131 Bos-Herce|date=16 June 2014|accessdate=21 June 2014|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\nAt the [[2015 Copa Am\u00e9rica]] in Chile, Zabaleta sent in the cross from which his Manchester City teammate [[Sergio Ag\u00fcero]] headed the only goal of the game as Argentina defeated holders [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] in their second [[2015 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group B|group]] match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/33085567|title=Argentina 1\u20130 Uruguay|date=17 June 2015|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nZabaleta was born in [[Buenos Aires]], to a family of [[Spain|Spanish]] (Basque) descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.euskalkultura.com/espanol/noticias/el-delantero-uruguayo-diego-forlan-su-abuela-vasca-y-sus-deseos-de-fichar-por-el-athletic-club-de-bilbao|title=El delantero uruguayo Diego Forl\u00e1n, su abuela vasca, y sus deseos de fichar por el Athl\u00e9tic Club de Bilbao|publisher=EuskalKultura.com}}</ref> Zabaleta has a tattoo on his chest which bears the name of his mother.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pablo Zabaleta espera duro partido para Argentina contra Holanda|url=https://ecodiario.eleconomista.es/global/noticias/702153/08/08/Pablo-Zabaleta-espera-duro-partido-para-Argentina-contra-Holanda.html|newspaper=El Economista|date=13 August 2008|accessdate=30 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2018, he worked as a pundit for the BBC's [[Match of the Day]] [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 World Cup]] coverage from Russia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44568837|title=World Cup 2018: 'Everyone is so angry' \u2013 Pablo Zabaleta reacts to Argentina defeat|date=21 June 2018|accessdate=22 June 2018|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>.\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 19 February 2020}}<ref>{{cite web|title=P. Zabaleta|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/pablo-javier-zabaleta-girod/3259/|website=Soccerway|accessdate=13 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|Cup{{efn|Includes [[Copa del Rey]], [[FA Cup]], [[EFL Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2|Continental{{efn|Includes [[Copa Libertadores]], [[Copa Sudamericana]], [[Recopa Sudamericana]], [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup/Europa League]], [[UEFA Champions League]]}}\n!colspan=2|Other{{efn|Includes [[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]], [[FA Community Shield]]}}\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=4|[[San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]]\n|[[2002\u201303 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2002\u201303]]\n|[[Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]\n|11||0||colspan=2|\u2014||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||12||0\n|-\n|[[2003\u201304 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2003\u201304]]\n|Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n\n|27||3||colspan=2|\u2014||3||0||colspan=2|\u2014||30||3\n|-\n|[[2004\u201305 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2004\u201305]]\n|Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n\n|28||5||colspan=2|\u2014||9||0||colspan=2|\u2014||37||5\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n! 66 !! 8 !! 0 !! 0 !! 13 !! 0 !! 0 !! 0 !! 79 !! 8\n|-\n| rowspan=4|[[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]]\n|[[2005\u201306 La Liga|2005\u201306]]\n|[[La Liga]]\n|27||2||1||0||7||0||colspan=2|\u2014||35||2\n|-\n|[[2006\u201307 La Liga|2006\u201307]]\n|La Liga\n|20||0||0||0||9||0||2||0||31||0\n|-\n|[[2007\u201308 La Liga|2007\u201308]]\n|La Liga\n|32||1||4||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||36||1\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n! 79 !! 3 !! 5 !! 0 !! 16 !! 0 !! 2 !! 0 !! 102 !! 3\n|-\n| rowspan=10|[[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]\n|[[2008\u201309 Manchester City F.C. season|2008\u201309]]\n|[[Premier League]]\n|29||1||2||0||11||0||colspan=2|\u2014||42||1\n|-\n|[[2009\u201310 Manchester City F.C. season|2009\u201310]]\n|Premier League\n|27||0||8||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||35||0\n|-\n|[[2010\u201311 Manchester City F.C. season|2010\u201311]]\n|Premier League\n|26||2||8||0||11||0||colspan=2|\u2014||45||2\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Manchester City F.C. season|2011\u201312]]\n|Premier League\n|21||1||5||0||5||0||0||0||31||1\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Manchester City F.C. season|2012\u201313]]\n|Premier League\n|30||2||6||1||5||0||1||0||42||3\n|-\n|[[2013\u2